e.     Enter Divisions – Abbreviation, Description, Placing code
g.     Enter Flights/Groups you will use in your contest

2.     Before the contest, insert your Contest logo into the Awards sheet - change font, background and text colors.
a.     If you copy/paste data into the Weigh-in sheet, paste Values only to preserve formatting and validation. Red Text indicates an error.
i.    Click Print Cards button on Weigh-in sheet to print cards with data
ii.    For blank cards, go to the SpeakersCard sheet and click Print Blank Cards
c.      Do not leave blank rows between Lifters
d.     Click the button at the top of the sheet to copy weighed-in athletes to the Lifting sheet
a.     Select the 1st flight/group from the pulldown in cell A11
b.     Select Squat 1, Benchpress 1 or Deadlift 1 from the pulldown
c.      Select the an option to advance to the next lifter - Auto, Delay, Man
i.    Auto to advance without delay after a Good or NoLift
ii.    Delay for livestreamed contests – then select a Delay time (2-5 seconds)
iii.    Man for manual advance during 3rd attempts – then click Next to advance to the next lifter
e.     Use Ctrl + G (good) or Ctrl + N (no-lift) to go back and fix an incorrect entry
f.      Add DQ to Events Entered column for disqualified lifters. Add DT to the events for a drug tested lifter.
g.     Re-attempts - type the weight in the cell when a re-attempt is granted
i.    Use the dropdown menu in the name block (cell A1) to select a lifter for a re-attempt
h.     Printouts - Use the dropdown menu next to the printer icon to select the type of printout desired – click the printer icon to print
i.       Select Sorted Results at the end of the lifting session for a sorted printout (this step is necessary to load data for the Awards sheet. Have the referees sign a printout of this sheet.
5.     Awards sheet. Use the dropdown menu to select the awards to display (only the divisions, weight classes, and events actually used in the contest will be in the menu)
